'''Level 480''' was discovered by [[Backroom Colonists|The Backroom Colonists]] on 24th of July 2012 and [[M.E.G.]] fully completing exploration of '''Level 480''' on 3rd of December 2015. There are rumors that the level was discovered as early as 1945, but it is unconfirmed.

'''Level 480''', when found by The Backroom Colonists, appeared to be a habitable level with stable temperatures and everlasting sunlight, not the dark, anomalous hellscape it is now. Initial exploration of the level was made easy by the habitable nature of the level at the time, so exploration was carried out in a swift manner before confirming that '''Level 480''' was suitable for human life. The level was given a survival difficulty of Class 1, mainly due to discovered events on the level labeled “Storm Events." (Read Information Document 2 for context)

Eventually, after the discovery of the level, due to the level’s habitable nature and easy entrances and exits, many groups began to make Level 480 their home and settle down as much as possible, finding refuge in the liminal horror of the Backrooms. Eventually, a year after discovery, '''Level 480''' had become a hotspot for wanderer traffic, with many colonies, outposts, and trading sites. Life in '''Level 480''' appeared to be normal until IT happened. (Read Information Document 3 for context)
