{{Class 1}}

'''Level 480''' is the 481st level in the Backrooms.

==Description==
'''Level 480''', also known as “Sunlight”, resembles an average liminal rural area resembling areas of the Midwestern United States. The area of '''Level 480''' is not infinite and appears to be roughly in the same shape and area as the American states of Indiana, Ohio, Michigan, and Kentucky, with the areas around those states being vast oceans. '''Level 480''' also appears to share similar biomes with the states inside '''Level 480’s''' area, including mountains, lakes, rivers, plains, and hills. Multiple towns and cities are scattered across '''Level 480’s''' land area, which appears to have been placed at the exact point of their [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] counterparts and seems to be in the same condition as the present day, the only thing missing being people.

'''Level 480''' is perpetually locked in daytime, with the sun being at almost 90 degrees in the sky. Numerous clouds dot the sky, with most being white fluffy clouds. When one enters '''Level 480''', they will be present in front of a house in “Tillmook Michigan” with the address: "506 Preston Street, Tillamook, Michigan, ASU." As of right now, it is unknown what “ASU” actually is, but it’s theorized to be the alternative universe that '''Level 480''' is presented in.

Many rivers and streams are present throughout '''Level 480''', which mimics the shapes of the Ohio river, the Illinois river, and the ocean surrounding the level. However, the rivers do not contain water; instead, they consist of a compound known as “Not Water”. Not Water is a liquid that looks and feels like water, but one is able to walk on it for quite some time unless they directly stand on it, which causes one to sink below the surface level. One also cannot swim across Not Water, as they will sink below the environment and drown.

Multiple types of events on the level, known as “Storm Events” usually take place on '''Level 480''' from time to time. Most of the Storm Events resemble traditional storms from the Frontrooms, although with differences. Most Storm Events last up to 20 minutes, though there are some that could last for three or four months at a time. Storm Events are varied and are categorized into different types of storms. These are the different types of storms that could take place during a Storm Event:

*Thunderstorm: (very common)

*Tornado: (less common)

*Hurricane: (rare)

*Freak Storm: (very rare)

==Entities==
At this moment, no entities exist on '''Level 480'''.
==Colonies and Outposts==

===Trading Post 480===
A base operated by standalone merchants, Trading Post 480 is the first of many trading posts operated by the Backrooms Merchants. Trading Post’s 480 main objective is to allow people a place to rest and trade. Trading Post 480 is located in the “Indianapolis” area of Level 480, and is placed near where the capitol building exists in the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]], so it a bit of a walk from the level’s entrance.

===Base Midwest===
Base Midwest is a M.E.G. base set up on '''Level 480''' near the level’s entrance. Base Midwest is located in the area known as “Detroit” in the Frontrooms. The base is mainly set up on the edge of the city, where the Ambassador Bridge exists in the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]]. They are also very friendly and open to trade.

There are many more bases on Level 480, but they are the two biggest ones.

==Entrances==
*Entering a house with the same address as '''Level 480’s''' entrance house will lead here.
*Exiting out of any suburban house has a chance to lead one here, but the most likely route is through [[Level 53]].
*A metal door in [[Level 479]] will lead one here.
*One could enter this level from [[Level 499]] by an unknown fashion.

==Exits==
*If one sees a bridge leading into huge amount of fog in the distance, walking across it will lead one to [[Level 500]].
*Entering a suburban house with the address number “9” will lead one to [[Level 9]].
*Consuming pink cotton candy leads one to [[Level 9.2]].
*Entering a parking garage style structure will lead one to [[Level 1]].
*Noclipping into a car will lead one to [[Level -202]] after a long fall.

