On November 26, 2021, a major event unfolded in '''Level 480''' that would change everything forever. At this moment, the exact details of the event are unknown, and we are currently investigating everything. However, it seems like the event was the result of some physical interference with '''Level 480'''. The event itself caused the entirety of '''Level 480''' to become the hellscape of crisscrossing roads that it is today. Sub documents referring to the event are listed below:

{{Collapse|num=10|initial='''>Open Informational Document 3.1: EVENTLOG?'''|final='''>Close Informational Document 3.1: EVENTLOG?'''|body=
<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 5px; border:3px solid #FF0000; border-radius: 3px"><span style="text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">
'''Foreword:''' The following is a log of all phenomena that has occurred over the course of the event on November 26th, observed by M.E.G Base Midwest.
{{Underline|FF0000}}
'''Date:''' 26/11/21

'''Description:''' At approximately 3:00 hours on '''Level 480''', the sky suddenly and without warning turned black, including clouds, the supposed sun on the level, and ANY light. The level appeared to maintain its habitable state for a few hours after this event before reporting instability.

'''Notes:''' Declared the beginning of the 26/11/21 event.
{{Underline|FF0000}}
'''Date:''' 27/11/21

'''Description:''' Subjects on '''Level 480''' have reported houses and other buildings disappearing when they are looked away from, which is later revealed to be permanent a few minutes into this stage of the event. Residents of '''Level 480''' scrambles to find exits out of the level.

'''Notes:''' None
{{Underline|FF0000}}
'''Date:''' 28/11/21

'''Description:''' A large part of the geography of '''Level 480''' began to shift. As the buildings continued to disappear, the level’s roads seemed to have started twisting and shifting into new places, creating confusing layouts. A decrease in Storm Events began to happen around this time, with the last one happening on 24/11/21.

'''Notes:''' Assumed to be the climax of the 26/11/21 event
{{Underline|FF0000}}
'''Date:''' 29/11/21

'''Description:''' A large part of the geometry becomes unstable as the land structure and shape of the level itself becomes very unstable as it shifts and compacts into the “Water” to create new land. Level structure has appeared to act like water.

'''Notes:''' The inhabitants of Base Midwest began to leave when the level was still stable enough for a hastily made noclip. As a result, this is the last documentation we have on the level itself from the base.
</div>
}}

