<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 5px; border:3px solid #FF0000; border-radius: 3px"><span style="text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">
'''Foreword:''' The following is a log of a successful attempt at a post-event exploration occurring on the 30th of July 2023, after '''Level 480''' was confirmed to be safe enough for exploration attempts by a wanderer who had accidentally noclipped through an unstable “drop spot” on [[Level 1]]. At the time, it was unknown that the newly discovered level was the remnant of the original '''Level 480''', and thus it was classified under Pending Approval 345 until a numerical designation was found. However, after exploration of the new '''Level 480''', agents discovered numerous similarities to the original '''Level 480''', including the house, the initial geography, and the entry house and towns, and thus it was put under the '''Level 480''' slot.

Here is the log of the initial exploration of '''Level 480''', depicting the trials and tribulations of two expeditioners from the [[M.E.G.|Major Explorer Group]]:
{{Underline|FF0000}}

<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> Alright, we've tried so many times and almost got killed. Are you sure this is the door that leads to this supposed '''Level 480'''?<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> Positive. This is our way out of the [[Level 570|locked-up retail nightmare]].<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> If we're doing this, we must hold our hands together, so we both noclip at the same time.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> Let's do this.<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> On three, two, one.<br><br>

<center><div class="image">[[File:Glitch-image-1711714085.png|480px|link=]]</div></center>




<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> What... happened... here?<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> It's worse than we expected.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> I feel like we just got dropped on top of a stereotypical United States urban freeway interchange.<br>
<br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> I mean, it's just a road. Usually, even in the most chaotic American urban interchanges, going straight almost always leads one out onto open space.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> Well, it's the Backrooms after all. Even if we do find our way into a more free area, how do we get down from the freeway bridge?<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> That, I cannot answer. Let's just hope and pray we make it out of this highway hell. Let's get going.<br><br>
<center>''The two women walk through the desolate freeways, entering a desolate straight bend riddled with lanes and walls.''<br><br></center>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> This freeway is so wide. I think we might have to climb over these rough concrete barriers to get on a ramp leading to the level proper.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> That's not really a good idea. We're not that good at climbing over barriers.<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> What other option do we have? We've been walking for twenty whole minutes. The freeway has no end in sight.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> Well, whatever we must do. The desolate highway gives me strong vibes of that [[Level 777|dark hellhole]].<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> We must act fast, lest we actually end up in that urban Gehenna.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> Okay, we should do it. I see an exit ramp over there.<br><br>


<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> That was grueling. I almost feel like I scarred my elegant body.<br><br>
<span style="color:indianred; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Mackenzie:'''</span> Looks are the least of our worries, at least we're here now. We must gather as much information on this novel discovery before anything bad happens to us.<br><br>
<span style="color:mediumblue; text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.25em black, 0em 0em 0.25em black">'''Bianca:'''</span> I feel like we should go to that commercial area over there.<br><br>

